[5] France (Burgundy-Franche-Comte/Dijon)
Date: Wed 3 Jul 2019 22:44 CEST
Source: Le Bien Public [in French, trans. Corr SB, edited]
https://www.bienpublic.com/cote-d-or/2019/07/03/fontaine-les-dijon-plusieurs-cas-de-coqueluche-confirmes


This Wednesday morning [3 Jul 2019], several parents in Cote-d'Or [Burgundy-Franche-Comte/Dijon] attending a welcoming ceremony for children in the institutions infancy and schools of Fontaine-les-Dijon received a briefing note from the Regional Health Agency (ARS) of Burgundy-Franche-Comte (BFC). This message indicated that "several cases of whooping cough have been reported for children attending a kindergarten school in Fontaine-les-Dijon, some of whom attend the Les Saverney leisure center. This bacterial respiratory disease is very contagious and likely to cause complications, especially in the most fragile (infants, people with respiratory diseases. or immunosuppressed). It requires the implementation of measures to prevent its spread.

The ARS BFC added that as a precaution, it advised parents to: "Check, with the help of your doctor, that your child is well vaccinated against whooping cough and if necessary, have the vaccine updated by the doctor; Check with your doctor if your child has a cough by reporting this situation of group cases of whooping cough."

In detail, the ARS BFC, contacted on this subject on [Wed 3 Jul 2019], told us that "since the end of May [2019], 9 confirmed cases of pertussis" have been reported to him "among the students of the nursery school of the Portfolios of Fontaine-les-Dijon and Les Saverney leisure center. The institution continued: "Children have benefited from medical treatment adapted to this respiratory disease caused by a bacterium, responsible for frequent and prolonged coughing spells. No cases have been reported in other schools or recreation of Fontaine-les-Dijon."

--
